PHASE 4 DATA PIPELINE SCRIPTS - INDEX
=====================================

This directory contains all real data collection scripts for backtest v2 rebuild.

SCRIPTS (5 total, 772 lines Python)
====================================

1. fetch_binance_vision.py (186 lines, 6.4 KB)
   - Downloads BTCUSDT OHLCV candles (1m/1h/1d) + funding rates
   - Source: https://data.binance.vision (free API)
   - Output: Parquet files, ZSTD compressed
   - Coverage: 2020-01 to present (6+ years)
   - Time: ~30 minutes for full download
   - Usage: python fetch_binance_vision.py

2. fetch_coinalyze.py (169 lines, 5.3 KB)
   - Downloads Open Interest (daily/hourly) + Liquidations (hourly)
   - Source: https://coinalyze.net (free API)
   - Output: Parquet files, ZSTD compressed
   - Includes: Long liquidations, Short liquidations, Total USD
   - Time: ~5 minutes
   - Usage: python fetch_coinalyze.py

3. fetch_fred.py (105 lines, 3.3 KB)
   - Downloads macroeconomic indicators
   - Series: DFF (Fed funds), DGS10 (Treasury), WALCL (Balance sheet), CPIAUCSL (CPI)
   - Source: https://fred.stlouisfed.org (free API key)
   - Key: Instant free signup at https://fred.stlouisfed.org/docs/api/api_key.html
   - Time: ~10 seconds
   - Usage: export FRED_API_KEY=key && python fetch_fred.py

4. fetch_fear_greed.py (62 lines, 1.8 KB)
   - Downloads Crypto Fear & Greed Index
   - Source: https://api.alternative.me (free)
   - Coverage: Full history in single API call
   - Time: ~1 second
   - Usage: python fetch_fear_greed.py

5. validate_data_integrity.py (250 lines, 8.1 KB)
   - Quality assurance for all downloaded data
   - Checks: Timestamp gaps, price anomalies, missing values
   - Output: Markdown report in docs/data_quality_report.md
   - Time: ~1 minute
   - Usage: python validate_data_integrity.py

DOCUMENTATION (3 files)
========================

- README.md          Quick reference guide + source table + troubleshooting
- QUICKSTART.md      30-second setup + 2-minute FRED key instructions
- .INDEX            This file

QUICK START
===========

All data:
  python fetch_binance_vision.py
  python fetch_coinalyze.py
  python fetch_fear_greed.py
  export FRED_API_KEY=key && python fetch_fred.py
  python validate_data_integrity.py

Or via Docker:
  docker compose --profile backtest run --rm backtester \
    python scripts/data/fetch_binance_vision.py

DATA LOCATIONS
==============

cryptoengine/data/
├── binance_vision/
│   ├── klines/BTCUSDT/{1m,1h,1d}/{year}/{month}.parquet
│   └── funding/BTCUSDT/{year}-{month}.parquet
├── coinalyze/
│   ├── open_interest/BTCUSDT_{daily,hourly}.parquet
│   └── liquidations/BTCUSDT_hourly.parquet
├── fear_greed/
│   └── fear_greed_index.parquet
└── fred/
    └── {DFF,DGS10,WALCL,CPIAUCSL}.parquet

